Th36: (for A being (Subset-Family of PM) holds (A c= ( Family_open_set PM ) implies ( union A ) in ( Family_open_set PM )))
proof
let A being (Subset-Family of PM);
assume A1: A c= ( Family_open_set PM );
(for x holds (x in ( union A ) implies (ex r st (r > ( 0 ) & ( Ball (x,r) ) c= ( union A )))))
proof
let x;
assume x in ( union A );
then consider W being set such that A2: x in W and A3: W in A by TARSKI:def 4;
reconsider W as (Subset of PM) by A3;
consider r such that A4: r > ( 0 ) and A5: ( Ball (x,r) ) c= W by A1,A2,A3,CKB31:def 1;
take r;
thus r > ( 0 ) by A4;
W c= ( union A ) by A3,ZFMISC_1:74;
hence thesis by A5,XBOOLE_1:1;
end;
hence thesis by CKB31:def 1;
